## 2. TYPOGRAPHY

Font family: **Figtree** (Google Fonts) — NEVER use any other font.

### Type Scale (Figma Variables → Typography — EXACT VALUES)

Each size level has weight variants. Line heights and letter spacing are EXACT from Figma variables.

| Figma Style         | Size  | Line Height | Letter Spacing | Available Weights                                              |
|---------------------|-------|-------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------------------------|
| Extra Tiny 10       | 10px  | 12px        | 0              | Regular, Medium, SemiBold, Bold                                |
| Tiny 12             | 12px  | 16px        | 0              | Regular, Medium, SemiBold, Bold                                |
| Small 14            | 14px  | 20px        | 0              | Regular, Medium, SemiBold, Bold                                |
| Regular 16          | 16px  | 24px        | 0              | Regular, Medium, SemiBold, Bold                                |
| Medium 20           | 20px  | 28px        | 0              | Light, Regular, Medium (Sub heading), SemiBold (Card-Title), Bold, ExtraBold, Black |
| Medium 24           | 24px  | 30px        | -0.15px        | Regular, Medium, SemiBold, Bold                                |
| Large 32            | 32px  | 38px        | -0.2px         | Regular, Medium, SemiBold, Bold                                |
| Large 40            | 40px  | 48px        | -0.3px         | Regular, Medium, SemiBold, Bold                                |
| Extra Large 48      | 48px  | 58px        | -0.4px         | Regular, Medium, SemiBold, Bold                                |
| Title 72            | 72px  | 84px        | -0.8px         | Regular, Medium, SemiBold, Bold                                |

### Named Typography Variants (Medium 20 group)
- `Regular` → font-normal (400), 20/28
- `Sub heading Medium` → font-medium (500), 20/28
- `Card-Title SemiBold` → font-semibold (600), 20/28
- `Bold` → font-bold (700), 20/28
- `ExtraBold` → font-extrabold (800), 20/28
- `Light` → font-light (300), 20/28
- `Black` → font-black (900), 20/28

### Tailwind Mapping
```
text-extra-tiny  → 10px / 12px line-height
text-tiny        → 12px / 16px line-height
text-small       → 14px / 20px line-height
text-regular     → 16px / 24px line-height
text-medium      → 20px / 28px line-height
text-medium-lg   → 24px / 30px line-height, -0.15px tracking
text-large       → 32px / 38px line-height, -0.2px tracking
text-large-xl    → 40px / 48px line-height, -0.3px tracking
text-extra-large → 48px / 58px line-height, -0.4px tracking
text-title       → 72px / 84px line-height, -0.8px tracking
```
All line-heights and letter-spacing are baked into the Tailwind fontSize config.
Just use the class — no need for separate leading-* or tracking-* classes.

