## 6. CODING RULES

### Component Architecture
- Use **server components** by default
- Use `'use client'` ONLY when needed (onClick, useState, forms, animations)
- Keep components small, reusable, typed with TypeScript
- Match Figma component names where possible (e.g., EventCard, NavBar, Badge)

### Styling Rules
- Use **Tailwind CSS ONLY** — no inline styles, no CSS modules, no styled-components
- Use semantic token classes from `tailwind.config.ts` (e.g., `bg-page`, `text-primary`, `border-default`)
- When Figma has an exact value not in Tailwind defaults, use arbitrary values: `text-[32px]`, `p-[64px]`
- **Mobile-first**: base styles for Phone (412px), scale up with `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`
- NEVER add colors, shadows, or decorative elements not in the Figma design

### File Structure
```
src/
├── app/
│   ├── layout.tsx              (root layout — Figtree font, metadata)
│   ├── page.tsx                (landing page)
│   ├── globals.css             (base styles, custom components)
│   ├── (auth)/
│   │   ├── sign-in/page.tsx
│   │   ├── sign-up/page.tsx
│   │   └── reset-password/page.tsx
│   └── (dashboard)/
│       ├── events/page.tsx     (view all events)
│       ├── event/[id]/page.tsx (event detail)
│       └── search/page.tsx     (search + filters)
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                     (Button, Input, Badge, Card, Tag)
│   ├── layout/                 (Navbar, Footer, Container, PageWrapper)
│   └── sections/               (Hero, Features, Stats, Categories, CTA, HowItWorks)
├── lib/
│   ├── supabase.ts
│   └── utils.ts
└── types/
    └── index.ts
```

### Design Direction
- **Editorial dark** aesthetic — NOT generic SaaS
- **Premium and minimal** — clean whitespace, structured hierarchy
- **Neutral-driven** — NO loud colors, no gradients unless explicitly in Figma
- No shadows unless explicitly defined in Figma effect styles
- The product should feel like a **curated design culture layer**

### When Converting From Figma
1. ALWAYS use the Figma MCP to fetch exact design data
2. Use SEMANTIC token classes (`bg-surface`, `text-muted`, `border-default`) not raw hex
3. Match spacing pixel-for-pixel
4. Match typography exactly — size, weight, color, line-height
5. Implement ALL 4 responsive breakpoints
6. Reuse components — if a pattern repeats in Figma, make it a React component
7. Match exact border-radius values from Figma
8. Do NOT add decorative elements not present in the design
9. Do NOT change the visual hierarchy or layout
10. Test at all breakpoints: 412px, 768px, 1440px, 1920px

### Accessibility
- Semantic HTML: nav, main, section, article, aside, footer
- Proper heading hierarchy: h1 → h2 → h3 (one h1 per page)
- Alt text on all images
- focus-visible states using `border-focused` token
- aria-labels on icon-only buttons
- Keyboard navigation support
